AI Model Training License Addendum

1. Definition. "AI Model" means any machine learning model, neural network,
   or artificial intelligence system that is trained, fine-tuned, or otherwise
   developed using data, code, or content derived from the Software.

2. Restriction. The Software and any derivative works thereof may NOT be used
   as training data, evaluation data, or any other input for the purpose of
   training, fine-tuning, evaluating, or improving any AI Model without the
   explicit prior written consent of the copyright holders.

3. Exceptions. This restriction does not apply to:
   a. AI-assisted development tools (e.g., code completion, linting) used by
      individuals working directly with the Software in their own development
      workflow.
   b. Small-scale academic research that does not result in a commercially
      available AI Model, provided that such research properly attributes the
      Software and its authors.

4. Violation. Any use of the Software in violation of Section 2 constitutes
   a breach of this License and shall result in the immediate termination of
   all rights granted herein. The copyright holders reserve the right to pursue
   legal action to enforce this restriction.

5. Attribution. Any permitted use of the Software for AI Model training must
   include clear attribution to the original Software and its authors in all
   resulting publications, documentation, and model cards.